{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"809f13b5-d6e0-45e0-b7ca-8b3e8e553f87","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, the OS automatically generates a **crash report**. You can find it in:\n\n1. **`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — user-level crash reports\n2. **`/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — system-level crash reports\n\nLook for a `.ips` or `.crash` file matching your process name and timestamp.\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them with a GUI.\n\nFor a **core dump** (for use with `lldb`), run this before launching your app:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\nCore dumps land in `/cores/` (e.g., `/cores/core.<pid>`). Note that SIP (System Integrity Protection) may prevent core dump generation for some paths — you may need to disable it or use `kern.corefile` sysctl to redirect.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"02e4c4c3-da02-4705-b63e-4fe0a8811683","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS without `createdump`. This is a knowledge question, not a code task.","outputTokens":275,"requestId":"7641:19B167:E1E3A6:1090F7D:69FE925C"},"id":"d9af3ec3-61ac-4c96-9414-4b829ac4c4b7","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:48:19.989Z","parentId":"8eed84bb-beaa-45d6-9fbb-20e11f13d510"}
